According to the documentation, to set the permissions of the account rds to read-only, with the associated schema name teste123, the following steps need to be taken:

1. Create the associated schema named teste123:
   Request example:
   ```
   { 
     "db_name" : "gaussdb_test", 
     "schemas" : [ { 
       "name" : "rds", 
       "owner" : "teste123" 
     } ] 
   }
   ```

2. Grant read-only permissions to the database account rds and associate it with the schema named teste123:
   Request example:
   ```
   { 
     "db_name" : "gaussdb_test", 
     "users" : [ { 
       "name" : "rds", 
       "readonly" : true, 
       "schema_name" : "teste123" 
     } ] 
   }
   ```

By following the above steps, the permissions of the account rds will be set to read-only and associated with the schema named teste123.
